A police officer has been charged with stealing police communication pocket phone. Innocent Ichalai was charged today before Kibera senior resident magistrate Charles Mwaniki where he pleaded not guilty to the charges. Ichalai the charge sheet says that he committed the offence on August 14 at Mathare area along Juja road jointly with others not before court. The charge sheet says that he stole one communication pocket phone make Huawei identification serial number53137009 and MEI number 864106020071601 valued at Sh130, 000 the property of the National police service. He however denied the charges and urged court to release him on lenient bond terms. The magistrate released him on a cash bail of Sh 100,000 or a bond of Sh 50, 000. The case willÂ  proceed on September 3.